            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pastry, filling, and assembly",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add 5 to 7 tablespoons of ice-cold water until the dough comes together. Divide into two discs, wrap, and refrigerate for 1 hour. Toss the chopped {{apple-bramley}} and {{pear-conference}} with the {{caster-sugar}}, {{cornflour}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, {{mixed-spice}}, and {{lemon-juice}}. Roll the larger pastry disc and line the pie dish. Fill with the fruit mixture, mounded generously. Top with the second rolled disc, trim, crimp, and cut vents.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 50 to 55 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Brush the top crust with {{eggs}} wash and scatter {{demerara-sugar}} over. Bake for 20 minutes at 200°C, then reduce to 180°C for a further 30 to 35 minutes until deep golden and the filling is bubbling through the vents. Cool on a rack for at least 1 hour before cutting. Serve warm or at room temperature with cream or custard.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
